title: Grateful Dead Live at Greek Theatre, Univ. of California on 1982-05-22
lineage: Cassette Master (Nakamichi DR-1) -> Sound Devices 744T (24bit/48k) -> Adobe Audition v3.0 -> -> Samplitude Professional v11.1 -> FLAC/16
description:
Set 1

Jack Straw-> Sugaree, Cassidy, Tennessee Jed-> Minglewood Blues, Cumberland Blues, Lazy Lightning-> Supplication-> Deal

Set 2

China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider-> Women Are Smarter, Good Time Blues, Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> He's Gone-> Drums-> Not Fade Away-> Wharf Rat-> Around & Around-> Good Lovin', E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text: Burning first set. Just listened  to the first set again on a bike ride, and it is absolutely smoking! Jerry is firing on all cylinders and Phil is too, and rest of the band follow suit. This is truly a gem, the recording is also top notch. All the guitars are really loud and clear, vocals a bit less so, but hey, it’s all good with a performance this inspired. Can’t really talk about set 2, but based on set 1 alone this is a standout from 1982.
